way we got to see the different sides of Margo, trying to work out which one really was her true self.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image element--thumbnail\" data-media-id=\"ac1aba8865ceb7a446c538b56119b523792fa3ae\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/8/26/1440583190216/6e605c20-4e1d-4d38-af3d-7f0212d39b91-275x420.jpeg\" alt=\"Paper Towns\" width=\"275\" height=\"420\" class=\"gu-image\" /> </figure>  <p>Please don’t judge me, but this is actually the first book I’ve read by John Green - I’m sure that he is about to come a regular on my bookshelf. </p> <p>5/5</p> <ul> <li><strong>Buy this book at the <a href=\"https://bookshop.theguardian.com/catalog/product/view/id/286234/s/paper-towns/\">Guardian Bookshop</a>.</strong><br /></li> </ul> <h2><strong>Want to tell the world about a book you’ve read? <a href=\"http://preview.gutools.co.uk/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">Join the site</a> and send us your review!</strong></h2>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"<strong>The Fanatical Reader: </strong>‘There were moments when I was scared, moments when I roared with laughter and moments when I questioned the sanity of everyone’","headline":"Paper Towns by John Green - review","byline":"The Fanatical Reader","commentable":"false","commentCloseDate":"2015-09-09T11:00:08Z","standfirst":"<p>‘There were moments when I was scared, moments when I roared with laughter and moments when I questioned the sanity of everyone’ </p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2015/sep/09/paper-towns-john-green-review","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/childrens-books-site/2015/sep/09/paper-towns-john-green-review","sectionName":"Children's books","tags":[{"id":"childrens-books-site/childrens-books-site","webTitle":"Children's books","type":"blog","sectionId":"childrens-books-site","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-sit